# Veda — AI-Powered PDF to Interactive Presentation Web App
# Cursor Rules File

## What This Project Is
Veda converts any uploaded PDF into an interactive narrated presentation with
karaoke-style word highlighting. The user uploads a PDF, the backend extracts
layout per page, a local Qwen 3B LLM generates slide JSON (title, subtitle,
summary, highlights, narration), and Sarvam AI handles TTS + STT for
word-level timestamps. The mascot is Zoro — a cartoon elephant avatar
(New_Zoro.png) to be animated via HeyGen Talking Photo API.

---

## Project Structure

```
veda/
  server/
    tts_server.py         ← Main FastAPI backend (port 8765)
    .env                  ← API keys (SARVAM_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY)
    vendor/               ← pip-installed packages (edge-tts, fastapi, torch, transformers, etc.)
    models/               ← Local GGUF model files (Qwen2.5)
    active_doc.pdf        ← Currently loaded PDF (written on upload)

  src/
    App.jsx               ← Root React component
    main.jsx              ← Vite entry point
    index.css             ← Global styles, amber/gold design system, Tailwind v4
    components/
      AIAvatar.jsx        ← Animated avatar component (to be replaced by Zoro video)
      LeftPanel.jsx       ← PDF TOC sidebar
      RightPanel.jsx      ← Main presentation + karaoke
    context/
      PDFContext.jsx      ← useReducer + Context API for global state
    utils/
      pdfUtils.js         ← PDF.js utilities, page analysis, image extraction
      speechUtils.js      ← Speech/audio utilities
  index.html              ← Loads Inter, Outfit, and Noto Sans Telugu from Google Fonts
```

