## Backend — tts_server.py (FastAPI, port 8765)

### API Endpoints
| Method | Path | What it does |
|--------|------|--------------|
| GET | /health | Health check |
| POST | /upload_pdf | Accepts raw PDF bytes, saves as active_doc.pdf, opens with PyMuPDF |
| GET | /page_layout?page=N | Returns { width, height, lines[], images[] } for page N |
| POST | /analyze | Runs local Qwen 3B LLM, returns slide JSON; translates to Telugu via NLLB-200 if language=te-IN |
| POST | /translate | Translates a list of strings using NLLB-200 (local), falls back to Sarvam |
| POST | /translate_deck | Translates a full slide deck to Telugu; NLLB-200 first, Sarvam fallback |
| POST | /tts | Sarvam TTS → returns { audio (base64 WAV), word_boundaries[] } |
| GET | /tts_stream | Streams audio (Sarvam or edge-tts fallback) |
| POST | /tts_boundaries | Returns only word_boundaries (no audio) |
| POST | /transcribe | OpenAI Whisper STT → returns { text, word_boundaries[] } |

### Key Classes & Functions
- `SarvamMemoryCache` — in-memory single-entry cache (text+lang+voice+rate as key)
- `LLMState` — singleton for llama-cpp Qwen 3B model, lazy-loads on first /analyze call
- `IndicTransState` — singleton for NLLB-200 translation model (facebook/nllb-200-distilled-600M),
  lazy-loads on first translation call; model already cached locally (downloaded Jul 1 2026), loads instantly
- `PDFMetadataAnalyzer` — detects repeating headers/footers across pages to filter them
- `detect_speech_boundaries(wav_bytes)` — finds lead-in/lead-out silence in WAV
- `adjust_boundaries_to_silence(boundaries, wav_bytes)` — corrects STT timestamps for Sarvam's 150-570ms padding
- `generate_fallback_boundaries(text, duration)` — proportional timestamp fallback if STT fails
- `analyze_text_semantic(text, is_digest, language)` — calls Qwen LLM, parses JSON response with auto-repair
- `translate_strings_indictrans2(texts, target_lang)` — translates using NLLB-200 locally (no API cost)
- `translate_strings_sarvam(texts, api_key)` — batch translates via Sarvam Translate API (fallback only)

### LLM Config
- Active model: Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct (GGUF, Q4_K_M quantization, ~2.1GB)
- Model size controlled by env var `LOCAL_LLM_SIZE` (0.5B / 1.5B / 3B) — currently 3B
- Loaded via llama-cpp-python with n_ctx=4096, n_threads=min(8, cpu_count)
- Model paths checked: server/models/ only (no hardcoded user paths)
- JSON auto-repair built in (_extract_json) because small models produce malformed JSON
- Auto-downloads model from HuggingFace on first /analyze call if not present

### Translation (NLLB-200)
- Primary: NLLB-200 distilled 600M (facebook/nllb-200-distilled-600M) running locally on CPU
- Why NLLB-200 instead of IndicTrans2: IndicTransToolkit requires MSVC C++ Build Tools to
  compile its Cython extension — not available on this Windows server. NLLB-200 works with
  plain transformers, no build tools needed.
- Language code map (INDICTRANS_LANG_MAP): te-IN → tel_Telu, hi-IN → hin_Deva, etc.
- Fallback: Sarvam Translate API if NLLB-200 fails or is not yet loaded
- All translation calls go through translate_strings_indictrans2() first

### Image Extraction (/page_layout)
- Uses PyMuPDF get_text("dict") to extract image blocks
- Images returned with: url (base64), x, y, w, h, cx, cy (centre coordinates)
- Coordinate system: bottom-up (y = height - bbox_bottom), same as text lines
- Filters applied before returning:
  - Skip images with near-zero dimensions (w < 5 or h < 5) — invisible artifacts
  - Skip images smaller than 80×80 — decorative icons, bullets, small logos
  - Skip images wider than 80% of page width — full-page backgrounds and decorative banners

### Known Issues / Things to Watch
1. SarvamMemoryCache is single-entry only — second unique request evicts the first
2. /transcribe uses OpenAI Whisper API (costs money) — Sarvam STT used for karaoke instead
3. CORS is wide open (allow_origins=["*"]) — fine for demo, restrict before production
4. NLLB-200 model (~2.3GB) — ALREADY DOWNLOADED to C:\Users\ads_eng5\.cache\huggingface\hub\models--facebook--nllb-200-distilled-600M\ on Jul 1 2026; loads from local cache instantly, no re-download needed
5. Qwen 3B model (~2.1GB) downloads on first /analyze call if not in server/models/
6. LLMState loads with n_gpu_layers not set — CPU only (no GPU on this server)

