2. **Video caching** — Cache by slide_id + language key, serve from /videos/{filename}
3. **GPU inference** — n_gpu_layers=-1 for llama-cpp when GPU is available

## Image Upscaling (Real-ESRGAN) — DONE (Jul 2 2026)
- `/upscale_image` POST endpoint in tts_server.py
- `server/rrdb_net.py` — minimal RRDBNet architecture (pure torch, no basicsr dependency)
- Model: RealESRGAN_x4plus.pth (~67MB) in server/models/ — 4× upscale, 23 RRDB blocks
- Tiled inference (256px tiles, 10px pad) keeps peak RAM ~1GB on CPU
- Input images capped at 1024px max side; outputs 4× of capped input
- Frontend: `upscaleImages()` in pdfUtils.js fires concurrently after page layout loads;
  upscaled data-URLs swap into pageDeck.images + topics[*].image once ready (progressive enhancement)
- Dependencies added to server/vendor/: Pillow, opencv-python-headless, torchvision

